What you need to know:

Petrol in Nairobi will now retail at Sh105.28, recording a fourth rise in a row since it hit a four-year low in May when it retailed at Sh83.33 per litre.Diesel will record its first drop since May to sell at Sh94.51 per litre starting today.Kerosene, which jumped Sh18 per litre last month will now retail Sh0.50 lower at Sh83.15 per litre in Nairobi.